703696f-a.title: Brooklyn: Clinton Street - Centre Street
703696f-a.text:
595-609 Clinton Street, east side, from and including Centre,
to and including Mill Streets. A view of frame houses. 595 is in
the background at Mill Street. The ground was used for gardens by
school children during the War. View No. 2 shows the west side of
the street. View No. 3 shows the same buildings as are seen in view
No. 1, but in the later view they appear slightly modernized.
July 4, 1930.
View 2: June 25, 1931.
View 3: June 9, 1938.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
